NUMBER 1251
NAME Final Rest
ASTRAL
DARKNESS
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
A wide cavern stretches ahead. On the far side is a dust-choked wall of dirt
and boulders, remnants of a massive large cave-in many years ago. Seated
in the center of the floor is a skeleton, its palms to the ground as it rests.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 716 ADJ1=264 VAL2=634
; rocky opening (out to Snowy Peak)
ITEM 1 390 ADJ1=222 ADJ2=584
; old weatherbeaten skeleton

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
The freezing and thawing of water over the passing seasons has gradually
widened a natural fissure, forming a broad opening.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 1
Many of this skeleton's bones have long been shattered or crushed, perhaps in 
some battle before the person's death. It still wears the tattered remains of 
a brown monk's robe, its empty eye sockets diligently watching the rock wall.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB SEARCH -1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER A dry voice echoes from the skeleton, "Beware......"
  ECHO OTHERS %N listens to something.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB TOUCH 1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO OTHERS %N looks towards the skeleton after touching it.
  ECHO PLAYER A dry voice echoes from the skeleton, "Welcome to my... home."
  PLREVENT 1
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO PLAYER A dry voice echoes from the skeleton, "In life I was called Hoder, Master of Clan Earth. I lived with my fellow monks in our monastery, which sits farther into the mountain. Together with..."
  PLREVENT 3
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO PLAYER A dry voice echoes from the skeleton, "...Clan Wind..."
  PLREVENT 1
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO PLAYER A dry voice echoes from the skeleton, "...Clan Fire..."
  PLREVENT 1
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO PLAYER A dry voice echoes from the skeleton, "...Clan Water..."
  PLREVENT 1
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO PLAYER A dry voice echoes from the skeleton, "...we lived a peaceful life, venturing outside for only food and other needs. We aided all weary travelers that happened upon us. Then one night they came....the Shukenja, followers of Clan Shadow."
  PLREVENT 3
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO PLAYER A dry voice echoes from the skeleton, "You see we were the Guardians of a great artifact known as the "Elemental Orb". It was this the Shukenja came for. All the clans were slaughtered in the attack. I alone escaped to the caves were I found..."
  PLREVENT 3
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO PLAYER A dry voice echoes from the skeleton, "...the Shukenja had brought some strange race of people, giant in size. I did battle my way through them to the point where you find me now, using the last of my power I called down the cave-in you see before you. It is more then a simple wall of rocks, it.."
  PLREVENT 3
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO PLAYER A dry voice echoes from the skeleton, "..holds back the giants from going out into this area of Andor and wreaking havoc on its people. As well it stops those such as yourself from possible death at the hands of the giants or the Shukenja. But if battle them you wish then please do so, and slay many in my name and the name of all they killed.."
  PLREVENT 3
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO PLAYER A dry voice echoes from the skeleton, "..to go farther you need only say...Spirits of Earth, let me pass."
  PLREVENT 1
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO PLAYER A dry voice echoes from the skeleton, "..and good luck to you %N."
ENDIF

IFSAY Spirits_of_earth,_let_me_pass.
  ECHO ALL The wall wavers and fades from view, creating a stone archway.
  NEWITEM 9 60 ADJ1=STONE VAL2=1252
ENDIF

IFSAY Spirits_of_earth,_let_me_pass
  ECHO ALL The wall wavers and fades from view, creating a stone archway.
  NEWITEM 9 60 ADJ1=STONE VAL2=1252
ENDIF

IFPREVERB GO 9
  MOVE 1252
  ECHO ALL The wall fades back into view.
  REMOVEITEM 9
ENDIF
