Large soot-stained rocks ring the edges of a deep hollow chiseled into the
stone floor. The pit has been filled with various woods, whatever was handy
at the time, and is kept continuously ablaze by adding more fuel to the
flames whenever the fire seems to be getting too low.
*DESCRIPTION END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 1
Easily big enough to fit a whole cow into, without cutting it up first, this 
gargantuan cauldron is just the thing for cooking a neverending pot of stew
