There is no logical reason how the water in able to counter gravity and travel
up the wall. An invisible force seems to prevent the water pooled on the floor
from flowing out of the room into the main hall.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 2
The flickering blue lightning makes no sound. A single tear-shaped droplet
of water is etched onto the flat, polished upper surface.
